---
import Layout from '../layouts/CV.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="CV — Liam Connors"
	description="Liam Connors — Curriculum Vitae"
>
	<h1>CV</h1>
	<p class="intro">
		Senior technical writer and documentation engineer with experience writing API references, developer guides, and tutorials for developer libraries and AI tools. I’ve built documentation sites from scratch and managed end-to-end testing and publishing workflows using MkDocs, Sphinx, Vale, and GitHub Actions. I’ve also added AI features such as a docs chatbot and optimized content for agent-based use.
	</p>

	<h2>Work Experience</h2>
<h3 class="role">Senior Technical Writer</h3>
	<p class="meta">at Plotly · Montreal, Canada · (Jul 2021 – Apr 2026)</p>
	<p class="role-summary">
		As a technical writer at Plotly, I was responsible for creating and maintaining documentation for the company's data viz products — writing user guides, API documentation, and tutorials. Collaborated closely with product managers, developers, and fellow technical writers to ensure documentation accuracy and consistency across multiple projects.
	</p>

	<p class="cat">Writing &amp; Content Creation</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Wrote user guides, tutorials, and API reference docs for Python frameworks and libraries.</li>
		<li>Wrote docs for AI tools, including prompt examples, concepts, and tips and tricks docs.</li>
	</ul>

	<p class="cat">Release Management</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Learned the Plotly.py release process, took ownership of it, and managed releases as part of writing the docs and release notes.</li>
	</ul>

	<p class="cat">Docs Infrastructure &amp; Tooling</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Researched and evaluated docs tooling options and migrated docs content to MkDocs.</li>
		<li>Built custom Python tooling to enable versioning of enterprise content across documentation sites.</li>
		<li>Added search to the docs using an external search provider, integrated it into an existing React component, and wrote GitHub action workflows to update the search indexes.</li>
	</ul>

	<p class="cat">Quality Assurance &amp; Testing</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Improved test coverage on the docs, including writing tests to validate integrations with a docs chatbot.</li>
		<li>Migrated docs tests from Selenium to Playwright and CircleCI to GitHub Actions to improve test reliability.</li>
		<li>Implemented Vale for style guide enforcement.</li>
	</ul>

	<p class="cat">AI for Documentation</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Used Claude to validate documentation against code and references.</li>
		<li>Used Claude to accelerate test coverage across documentation projects.</li>
		<li>Built a docs plugin that returned content as Markdown for AI and agent consumption.</li>
		<li>Added tests to catch documentation drift and poorly structured content.</li>
		<li>Used Claude to draft documentation for Python-to-JavaScript backports.</li>
	</ul>

	<p class="cat">Content Performance &amp; Feedback</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Implemented a Usersnap feedback widget to collect user input and identify documentation gaps.</li>
		<li>Analyzed Algolia search data to refine existing content and uncover new documentation opportunities.</li>
	</ul>

	<p class="cat">Professional Development</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Attended technical docs conferences, for example, AI the Docs 2025, to stay current with industry trends and emerging best practices.</li>
	</ul>

	<hr />
